Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a private residence in Vineyard Haven, Massachusetts. She discussed the importance of community and the need for people to come together to address the challenges facing the country. Harris highlighted the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion rights and its impact on states, as well as the broader issues of voting rights, LGBTQ rights, book bans, and attacks on immigrants. She emphasized the vulnerability of democracy and the need to fight for its preservation. Harris also acknowledged the role of elections in shaping the direction of the country and highlighted the accomplishments of the Biden administration, such as rejoining NATO and passing legislation on child tax credits and infrastructure. She called for support in the upcoming midterm elections to ensure the passage of key legislation related to women's health and voting rights.